text: Interstate 985 (I-985) is an auxiliary Interstate in the U.S. state of Georgia. I-985 is also known as the Sidney Lanier Parkway, named after Sidney Lanier. Its south end is at I-85 in Suwanee. Its north end is at U.S. Route 23 (US 23) in Gainesville. The highway is long. I-985 is the second-highest numbered Interstate, with I-990 in New York being higher. ==References== 985
